title: Lancaster Dems Poll Greeter Training
description:
Election Day poll greeting involves volunteers stationed outside polling places to welcome voters, provide sample ballots, and offer any needed assistance or information. This friendly presence ensures that voters feel supported and informed as they exercise their right to vote.

In local elections, where outcomes can hinge on a small number of votes, the role of poll greeters is crucial in maximizing voter turnout and ensuring a smooth voting experience.

Never poll greeted before? Don't worry, this training will provide you with the information and tools you need to be an effective poll greeter on Election Day.

Why is Poll Greeting Important?

- Voter Assistance: Poll greeters can answer last-minute questions, direct voters to the correct polling locations, and provide information on voting procedures, reducing confusion and wait times.

- Encouragement: A warm welcome can boost voter morale and reinforce the importance of their participation in the democratic process.

- Education: Poll greeters help ensure voters are informed about their choices before entering the polling place by distributing sample ballots and information about candidates or issues.

**Facilited by Lancaster City Dems for all Lancaster County Democratic Poll Greeters.

Rally to Defend our Social Safety Net-

Website: www.SaveSocialSecurity.Net

Rally to Save Social Security, Medicare & Medicaid – May 7 at 4 PM in West Chester, PA
WEST CHESTER, PA — Concerned citizens of Chester County will gather at 4 PM on Wednesday, May 7 at the Social Security Office, to demand an end to the systematic dismantling of America’s most vital safety net programs: Social Security, Medicare, and Medicaid.

The rally, organized by SaveSocialSecurity.Net, aims to draw attention to sweeping changes taking place under President Trump’s administration — many of which are being implemented without public debate and in ways that disproportionately harm seniors, the disabled, and low-income Americans.

Chaos by Design: Undermining the Social Security Administration
In just the first 100 days of Trump’s return to office, the Social Security Administration (SSA) has faced:

Stricter ID verification rules, revised three times in a single month

Office closures and massive staff reductions, with over 2,500 experienced employees taking buyouts

Planned cuts of 12% of SSA’s workforce, totaling nearly 7,000 jobs

Loss of institutional knowledge, which is critical to resolving complex claims

Reduced access to in-person and telephone services, forcing online-only interaction

These actions are justified as efforts to reduce fraud, despite no evidence of widespread abuse and SSA’s long-standing reputation as one of the most efficiently run federal agencies.

“This isn’t reform — it’s sabotage,” said Cynthia Sherbin, an advisor with SaveSocialSecurity.Net. “The real goal is to create frustration and dysfunction so privatization seems like the only solution.”

Privatization: A Corporate Boondoggle
As with Medicare Advantage, privatization would shift services into the hands of for-profit corporations, introducing:

Higher administrative costs

Greater risk and market exposure for retirees

Increased potential for fraud, not less

“Privatizing Social Security doesn’t fix the system — it feeds corporate greed,” Sherbin said. “It redirects guaranteed benefits into the hands of shareholders, while increasing bureaucracy and decreasing reliability.”

Solvency Myths and Real Solutions
Much of the fear-mongering about Social Security’s future ignores straightforward solutions. In 2025, only the first $176,100 of earned income is subject to Social Security tax, and passive income like stock dividends goes untaxed. By simply:

Raising the income cap  

OR

Including passive income of the wealthiest Americans, also known as (AKA) Billionaires!

...Social Security's long-term solvency can be secured without cutting a single benefit.

Medicaid in the Crosshairs
The third pillar of the safety net — Medicaid — is under attack as well. The latest House-passed budget includes an $880 billion cut to Medicaid, jeopardizing care for:

63% of nursing home residents

42% of all U.S. births

Millions of disabled and low-income Americans, including 37 million children in the U.S. are enrolled in Medicaid or CHIP

“These devastating cuts are not about reducing waste — they’re about making room for more tax breaks for the rich,” Sherbin said.

Join the Rally – May 7 at 4 PM
What: Rally to Save Social Security, Medicare, and Medicaid
When: Wednesday, May 7, 2025 | 4:00 PM
Where: Social Security Office, West Chester, PA

Concerned citizens, advocates, and community leaders are invited to attend and demand that these lifeline programs be protected — not gutted.

#SaveSocialSecurity #ProtectMedicare #DefendMedicaidFOR IMMEDIATE RELEASE

description:
Join Basic Rights Oregon (BRO) at Hillsboro Pride 2025! 

Every year, we invite members of our LGBTQ2SIA+ community and allies to join us to table at Pride. 

As we continue to see bans on our bodily autonomy, and bans on our ability to safely exist in public, we are embarking on a ballot measure campaign, Equal Rights for All. This campaign seeks to codify access to gender affirming care, reproductive healthcare, and marriage equality into the Oregon constitution. 

ER4A gives Oregon voters a chance to enshrine these values. We need to gather over 250,000 signatures to get on the ballot in 2026. Joining us at pride this year is a chance to celebrate and advocate for a better Oregon.

We will be collecting signatures, sharing our work, and giving away goodies to all who stop by our booth. 

We hope you'll join us! Contact jose@basicrights.org with questions.

title: 12 Days to Democracy! Info Mtg: 12-Day 120-Mile March - Philly to DC - June 16-28
description:
Zoom Informational meetings about June 16-28 march from Philly to DC

Democracy 12 aims to inspire concerned citizens of all stripes to rise up in peaceful, happy, and creative protest, and any time is a good time to register voters...especially when talking about democracy!

We are doing this by taking a walk–a rather long walk–from Philadelphia to DC.

That’s the big picture.

Here are our two big goals:

We hope to find a core group of 12 walkers.
This mission needs a human-powered spirit team, and this group has to be everything we want our democracy to be: peaceful, civil, inspired and inspiring. Committed and reliable. Ready to set aside ordinary things.

If you’re possibly interested in becoming part of the core team, reach out, check us out. We get that becoming a core walker is a dive-in decision, so it's probably best if you get a feel for who we are and what we are doing to make the core group a team that’s happily, totally into it. Accommodations and meals will be on a sliding-scale for this group, as we desire to have a diverse group joining us. If you cannot make the whole walk due to other obligations please don't let that stop you from inquiring.

​

We hope that our walk will inspire and support local creativity, community, and peaceful resistance, all along the way.
This is how our march becomes your march, and actually, it’s sort of like everyone’s march.

So many concerned citizens are already creating and connecting in peaceful, resolute resistance, and it's already making a difference...

Let's keep on keeping on.

Check out our website www.democracy12.com. We hope to see you soon!

Let's vote like Australia!  Use voterizer in any state to register or re-register voters for the next election.

title: Join DeKalb Dems at Juneteenth in Stonecrest
description:
The City of Stonecrest is celebrating Juneteenth bigger than ever before this year by hosting it's 3rd annual Juneteenth Celebration of Freedom on Saturday June 14, 2025.

DeKalb Dems will have a visibility tent and we need volunteers to assist with set up and act as Ambassadors who listen to citizen's concerns, offer ways we can support them, and talk about what they can do to safeguard our freedom.

Juneteenth commemorates the effective end of slavery in the United States. Two years after President Lincoln signed the Emancipation Proclamation, news reached Texas and, upon learning they were free, former slaves immediately began celebrating with prayer, feasting, song, and dance. The Juneteenth Celebration of Freedom will celebrate African American culture, heritage, and, most importantly, abolishment of slavery.

The Juneteenth Celebration of Freedom will feature an expanded kidz zone, live performances, food trucks, vendors, and fireworks show. It is a place for all races, nationalities, and religions to join hands and truthfully acknowledge a period in history that shaped and continues to influence our society today, according to a news release. This event is free and open to the public, and we encourage everyone to attend and learn more about the history and culture of Juneteenth!

Please sign up for a shift below and be a part of this Celebration of Freedom.

title: Stand Up for Democracy in Frisco

location.venue: Southeast Corner of Preston Rd and Gaylord Pkwy in Frisco

description:
The Collin County Democratic Party, in partnership with 50501, invites you to join us as we Stand Up for Democracy! This is a critical moment to raise our voices against the forces threatening our democracy, social security, constitutional rights, and the very foundations of our nation. While this event is sponsored by the Collin County Democratic Party, it is nonpartisan in nature, as we believe ALL Americans must be unified in this fight for our rights.

This Event WILL go on rain or shine!

### We’re taking a stand against:

- Donald Trump and his MAGA extremists, who continue to undermine free elections and push authoritarian agendas.

- Elon Musk, whose unchecked influence and platforming of far-right extremism endanger our democracy.

- The so-called Department of Government Efficiency (DOGE), a shadowy effort to dismantle vital government functions.

- All their enablers—corporate greed, voter suppression, attacks on marginalized communities, and the erosion of our civil liberties.

### Why Protest Now? 
Our democracy is under siege. Social Security is at risk. The Constitution is being twisted to serve the powerful. Donald Trump "doesn't know" if everyone deserves due process (hint: it's what we're DUE!). Whether it’s attacks on reproductive rights, climate inaction, or the relentless assault on truth and justice—we’ve had enough!

Join us to demand accountability, defend our freedoms, and fight for a future where democracy works for ALL of us—not just the wealthy and well-connected.

📢 Bring your signs, your anger, and your determination! Together, we will peacefully but assertively make our voices heard.

#StandUpForDemocracy #SaveOurFuture #DefendTheConstitution

📍 Location: Southeast corner of Preston Road and Gaylord Parkway in Frisco, TX. Feel free to park behind the Jared's Jewelers at 3110 Preston Rd, Frisco, TX 75034; we will congregate on the sidewalk on the SE corner of Preston and Gaylord.

📅 Date & Time: May 17th, 2025 9-11am

This is OUR democracy. Let’s fight for it! ✊
